cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a novel semi-supervised learning technique for classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of thresholding techniques and an ensemble decision support system, which are common in artificial intelligence research (cs.AI). The evaluation of the proposed approach is performed on image classification datasets, which could also place the paper in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning models, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
